WHICH(1)                         User Commands                        WHICH(1)

NAME
       which - locate a command

SYNOPSIS
       which [-a] [-s] NAME...

DESCRIPTION
       which  returns  the  pathnames  of  the  files  (or  links)  which
       would  be  executed  in  the  current environment, by searching
       the  PATH  for  matching  executable  files.

OPTIONS
       -a     print all matching pathnames of each argument

       -s     silent mode; no output, only return exit status

NOTES
       which  does  not  support  long-form  options.  It searches the
       directories in the PATH environment variable.  Shell builtins
       and aliases are not found by which.

EXIT STATUS
       0      if all specified commands were found

       1      if one or more commands were not found

       2      if an error occurred

AUTHORS
       LikeOS-64 project.

SEE ALSO
       sh(1), ls(1), find(1)

